RACE.RACE_TEXT: ASSINIBOIA DOWNS RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 64. Claiming Purse 10200. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 117 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.

CLAIM.OWNER: B and J Stable and Hicks Wanda

RACE.FOOTNOTES: QUEEN IN THE NORTH, well placed off rail, advanced between horses to force issue inside turn, steadied mildly in late turn when TAPITURE came over while opening up into stretch, rallied outside that rival, took over sixteenth pole, held gamely to wire. LADY CREATIVE advanced between horses to force issue issue turn, gave best outside stretch, made a bid from the sixteenth pole, couldn't get to the winner. TAPITURE WAY advanced wide, short lead outside turn, drifted in while opening up into stretch, gave way passing sixteenth pole. RUBYINTHESTARS trailed to stretch, rallied belatedly. SKY TIZZY had outside speed under pressure, gave way into turn, stalked bid battle inside, lacked rally. SEA OF LIFE forced pace inside early, gave way into turn, stalked bid battle off rail, faded. There was a STEWARDS INQUIRY regarding the incident turning into the stretch. There was no change.

Non-nominated horses can be made eligible by paying 1% of the purse plus missed nomination by May 16 to CTHS office or 10% of purse at time of entry, to the race office, plus enter and start fees.
